Corning Inc. said it is increasing by 25% the capacity of its optical-fiber manufacturing facility.
The company said the plant, in Wilmington, N.C., is a leading fiber-producing plant in the world. 

Corning said the increase is the first of several capacity expansions anticipated over the next 18 months. 

Corning is a telecommunications, specialty glass, ceramic products and laboratory-services concern. 

